id:
A valid Service Instance ID / CRN must be configured to create or list buckets.
If the Service Instance has not been created already, create it using CLI: ‘ibmcloud resource service-instance-create <instance-name> cloud-object-storage <plan> <location>’.
Alternatively, you can create it using the IBM Cloud UI: https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/cloud-object-storage?topic=cloud-object-storage-provision#provision-instance.
Get the CRN using: ‘ibmcloud resource service-instance <instance-name> --crn’.
Configure the CRN using: ‘ibmcloud cos config crn --crn <crn-value>’.
Verify the Service Instance ID / CRN using: ‘ibmcloud cos config list’.
translation:
Um ID/CRN da instância de serviço válido deve ser configurado para criar ou listar buckets.
Se a instância de serviço ainda não tiver sido criada, crie-a usando a CLI: ‘ibmcloud resource service-instance-create <instance-name> cloud-object-storage <plan> <location>’.
Como alternativa, é possível criá-la usando a interface com o usuário da IBM Cloud: https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/cloud-object-storage?topic=cloud-object-storage-provision#provision-instance.
Obtenha o CRN usando: ‘ibmcloud resource service-instance <instance-name> --crn’.
Configure o CRN usando: ‘ibmcloud cos config crn --crn <crn-value>’.
Verifique o ID/CRN da instância de serviço usando: ‘ibmcloud cos config list’.
